   "source": [
    "A continuación se presentan los principales tipos de gráficos para la visualización de información, los cuales esán disponibles en la mayoría de aplicaciones."
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 1,
   "id": "569b4696-4a1c-433b-98ca-9185a7b1baf5",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "import matplotlib.pyplot as plt\n",
    "import numpy as np"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 2,
   "id": "7d9d094c-5cc7-477a-9872-d218269a01eb",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [],
   "source": [
    "x = np.linspace(0, 10, 10)"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "96c7fe0f-1591-4de6-b79d-a1956279e4e4",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Estilos de línea\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 3,
   "id": "63f8ca74-7f25-430e-9acb-d9c0ddbd263d",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "linestyles = [\"solid\", \"dashed\", \"dashdot\", \"dotted\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i_style, style in enumerate(linestyles):\n",
    "    plt.plot(x, x + i_style, linestyle=style, label=style)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 4,
   "id": "7b1730c2-2f0c-4f0b-9d8a-99327aae5dd8",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 432x288 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "linestyles = [\"-\", \"--\", \"-.\", \":\"]\n",
    "\n",
    "for i_style, style in enumerate(linestyles):\n",
    "    plt.plot(x, x + i_style, linestyle=style, label=style)\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.legend()\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "markdown",
   "id": "7aa76d35-0522-4359-86db-1a341d5f4fd1",
   "metadata": {},
   "source": [
    "Marcadores\n",
    "---"
   ]
  },
  {
   "cell_type": "code",
   "execution_count": 5,
   "id": "77dcae9f-01b0-452a-88c0-5700def9184b",
   "metadata": {},
   "outputs": [
    {
     "data": {
      "image/png": "\n",
      "text/plain": [
       "<Figure size 288x1008 with 1 Axes>"
      ]
     },
     "metadata": {
      "needs_background": "light"
     },
     "output_type": "display_data"
    }
   ],
   "source": [
    "from matplotlib.lines import Line2D\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.figure(figsize=(4, 14))\n",
    "\n",
    "markers = [m for m, func in Line2D.markers.items()]\n",
    "\n",
    "text_style = dict(\n",
    "    horizontalalignment=\"right\",\n",
    "    verticalalignment=\"center\",\n",
    "    fontsize=14,\n",
    "    fontfamily=\"monospace\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "marker_style = dict(\n",
    "    linestyle=\":\",\n",
    "    color=\"0.8\",\n",
    "    markersize=12,\n",
    "    markerfacecolor=\"tab:blue\",\n",
    "    markeredgecolor=\"tab:blue\",\n",
    ")\n",
    "\n",
    "for y, marker in enumerate(markers):\n",
    "\n",
    "    plt.text(-0.5, y, repr(marker), **text_style)\n",
    "    plt.plot([y] * 3, marker=marker, **marker_style)\n",
    "    # plt.gca().margins(0.2)\n",
    "    plt.gca().set_axis_off()\n",
    "    plt.gca().invert_yaxis()\n",
    "\n",
    "plt.show()"
   ]
  },
